description: The aim is to reduce physical vulnerability, mainly by giving propoer training to selected members of local communities and local government so that they know how to react in the event of sudden flooding, and secondly by building up emergency first aid stocks.  Since human activity (i.e. deforestation) plays a big part in increasing physical vulnerability, local demonstration projects will be carried out to show people how to lessen their vulnerability.  The second factor adding to the region's vulnerability is the weakness of the regional, national and local institutions responsible for disaster preparedness.  Under this first Action Plan we shall focus only on local institutional strengthening
sourceObjects_Organization.name: European Commission
destinationObjects_GlobalCluster.name: Multi-sector
destinationObjects_Organization.name: Movimiento por la Paz, el Desarme y la Libertad
